The McEliece cryptographic system is only enabled for the Linux Qt 5.x project files.

To enable the system for other systems, please follow the following suggestions.

1. Create a special ntl target.

ntl.target = ntl.a
ntl.commands = cd ../../libNTL/unix.d/src && ./configure && $(MAKE)
ntl.depends =

Be careful on freeBSD systems.

ntl.commands = cd ../../libNTL/unix.d/src && ./configure CXX=clang++ && gmake

2. Modify DEFINES.

DEFINES	+= SPOTON_MCELIECE_ENABLED

3. Modify INCLUDEPATH and LIBS.

INCLUDEPATH	+= ../../libNTL/unix.d/include
LIBS		+= -L../../libNTL/unix.d/src -l:ntl.a

Be careful of OS X systems. Use Homebrew!

LIBS		+= -lgmp -lntl

4. Modify QMAKE_CLEAN.

QMAKE_CLEAN += ../../libNTL/unix.d/src/*.o

5. Modify QMAKE_EXTRA_TARGETS and PRE_TARGETDEPS.

QMAKE_EXTRA_TARGETS = libntru libspoton ntl purge
PRE_TARGETDEPS = libntru.so libspoton.so ntl.a
